    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>DEAL FOR COAL MINER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Henri E. Cauvin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cauvin, Henri E</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anglo American, one of world's largest mining concerns, reaches agreement with Shell Petroleum Co Ltd to acquire Shell Coal Holdings for $850 million to $900 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>One of the world's largest mining concerns, Anglo American, has reached an agreement with the Shell Petroleum Company Ltd. to acquire Shell Coal Holdings for $850 million to $900 million. Shell Coal, which was put on the block last year, operates several mines, all but one of them in Australia, and acquiring them will help Anglo increase production outside South Africa and expand distribution into the Indo-Pacific market.</p>
        <p>Henri E. Cauvin</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>One of the world's largest mining concerns, Anglo American, has reached an agreement with the Shell Petroleum Company Ltd. to acquire Shell Coal Holdings for $850 million to $900 million. Shell Coal, which was put on the block last year, operates several mines, all but one of them in Australia, and acquiring them will help Anglo increase production outside South Africa and expand distribution into the Indo-Pacific market.</p>
        <p>Henri E. Cauvin</p>
